result.execSummary:
The defendant Daiveon D Moore was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take >$500 - $5000), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Daiveon D Moore in court with Attorney Joseph James Dorlack.  Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a no contest plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Repeater enhancer is stricken.  Count #2 is dismissed and read-in.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Dorlack makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

30 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 152 days)    *consecutive to any other sentence*
  -  15 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  15 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISON 

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS   (CONCURRENT) -  transfer allowed to Milwaukee County

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with: Co-actors or Wal-Mart stores 
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

RESTITUTION:  $604.72 to Wal-Mart (Joint and several) (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($50.00) and remainder due as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)

COSTS:  $278.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

NOTE:  Defendant is allowed to report to probation and parole on Monday, October 24, 2016
